The paper deals with the problem of posterior collapse in variational autoencoders, which is a common issue in machine learning and specifically in deep learning. The paper proposes a new method called NC-VAE, which is based on the noise contrastive estimation algorithm. This method is evaluated on popular image and text datasets, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
